    • getLabel

      public String getLabel()
      Label for rows displaying entities in the policy comparison UI. The default implementation returns a string of the form entityTypeName:entityName (for example Policy:123-456). The entity type name is the display name of the entity type of the EntityDiff, which can be localized by adding a display key of the form entity.TypeName (for example entity.Policy). The entity name is constructed by calling getEntityName(entity.KeyableBean) on either the old value of the entity or, if that is null (as in an add), on the new value of the entity.

      Subclasses can choose to either override this implementation entirely or to override getEntityName(entity.KeyableBean) to affect just the entityName part of the label.

      Specified by:
      getLabel in interface DiffDisplay
      Returns:
      a string label, must never be null

    • getEntityName

      protected String getEntityName(T bean)
      Helper method to get the name for either the Source bean or the Compare bean to display in the policy refresh UI. The default implementation just calls bean.DisplayName but subclasses should override this method as needed to customize the way the entity appears in the policy refresh UI. Note that this method is called by the default implementation of getLabel(); if that default implementation is completely overridden this method will no longer be called.
      Parameters:
      bean - - either the Source or Compare bean for which we need a name
      Returns:
      String - the name to use for this bean in the policy refresh UI
